      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Peter S. Graham (1939-2004) was an American librarian, writer and professor.  He held 
		positions at Columbia University, Indiana University and the Research Libraries Group, and 
		was University Librarian at Syracuse University (SU) from 1998 to 2003.  He also taught 
		English and textual studies at SU from 2000 to 2003, and throughout his career served on 
		numerous advisory boards and governing bodies for organizations relating to libraries, 
		books and scholarly publication.  In his early twenties he became involved in the civil 
		rights movement, participated in sit-ins and protests, and was once arrested with Stokely 
		Carmichael.  He worked for Bayard Rustin as office manager during the organization of the 1963 
		March on Washington.</p></bioghist>
      
